{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AKu5NGU2z9y4s57BA3Br52","type":"tool_result","content":"37-- **Mix-and-match orchestration** ã each workflow task specifies its own driver (claude-code, codex, opencode) and model. Use Opus for complex architecture, Sonnet for routine implementation, Codex for cost-effective batch verification.\n38-- **Plugin ecosystem integration** ã gstack skills run inside Claude Code sessions, omo agents run inside OpenCode sessions. codeharness orchestrates at the framework level; plugins orchestrate within each framework.\n39:- **Live workflow visualization** ã the existing Ink TUI gains a schematic workflow graph (`implement ã verify ã loop[retry, verify]`) with highlighted current position, framework label per task, and cost/time per node.\n40-- **CLI-wrapping driver model** ã all target frameworks (Claude Code Agent SDK, `codex` CLI, `opencode` CLI) are wrapped uniformly. No framework exposes a programmatic SDK for external orchestration ã codeharness fills that gap by wrapping their CLIs and parsing their outputs.\n41-\n--\n111-| Driver health check | At workflow start, verify all referenced drivers are installed and authenticated |\n112-| TUI workflow graph | Ink component showing flow DAG with current position, framework labels |\n113:| Per-node cost/time in TUI | Each workflow node shows accumulated cost and elapsed time |\n114-| Loop iteration counter | TUI shows loop count on loop blocks |\n115-| Output contract passing | Serialize task output to JSON, feed as input to next task across framework boundary |\n--\n195-Story 1-1 begins. `implement` highlights.\n196-\n197:[Omitted long matching line]\n198-\n199-**Climax:** `verify` highlights ã `[codex]`. The Codex driver spawns `codex` CLI with the evaluator's prompt, no source access. The evaluator interacts with the running application, produces a Showboat proof. Three frameworks touched one story. The TUI shows all three nodes as completed with checkmarks, cost per node, and elapsed time.\n--\n250-| Journey | Capabilities Revealed |\n251-|---------|----------------------|\n252:| **Sasha ã Cross-Framework Verify** | Per-task driver/model in workflow YAML, driver abstraction, cross-framework output contract passing, TUI workflow graph with framework labels |\n253-| **Autonomous Loop ã Multi-Framework** | Driver factory, CLI spawning for each framework, stream event normalization across drivers, TUI multi-framework rendering, cost tracking per driver |\n254:| **Sasha ã TUI Watching** | Persistent workflow graph in TUI, current position highlighting, per-node cost/time, loop iteration counter, framework label per task node |\n255-| **Marcus ã New Driver** | `AgentDriver` interface, driver registration, CLI wrapping pattern, stream output parsing, <300 LOC per driver |\n256-\n--\n273-**4. Workflow-as-TUI: Live DAG Visualization**\n274-\n275:TUI tools for coding agents show activity logs (tool calls, text output). codeharness shows the workflow graph itself ã a schematic DAG with nodes, framework labels, cost/time per node, and \"you are here\" highlighting. This makes orchestration visible, not just activity.\n276-\n277-### Market Context & Competitive Landscape\n--\n405-- FR24: System can render a schematic workflow graph in the Ink TUI showing all tasks as nodes with directional flow\n406-- FR25: System can highlight the currently executing task node in the workflow graph\n407:- FR26: System can display the driver name (framework label) under each task node in the workflow graph\n408:- FR27: System can display accumulated cost and elapsed time per completed task node\n409-- FR28: System can render loop blocks in the workflow graph with visual grouping and iteration counter\n410:- FR29: System can update the workflow graph position within 500ms of a task transition\n411:- FR30: System can show task completion status (checkmark, spinner, pending) per node in the workflow graph\n412-\n413-### TUI Activity Display (Existing ã Extended)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AdiTT4z2ChkJFB9qFrkzAF","session_id":"87203133-5cdd-4288-8e5c-bcff0e178735","uuid":"ed10c063-33bd-467f-9a75-44a27cfab7ee","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:33:43.737Z"}
