{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012y7SjLuUxFFR3yngtjovKc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016PCr8YAABhp45KANjBn3b3","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-2-task-status-driver-labels.md","content":"# Story 14.2: Task Status & Driver Labels\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a user,\nI want each workflow node to show its status, driver name, and cost/time,\nso that I can see what is running, on which framework, and what it costs at a glance.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** a pending task in the workflow graph\n   **When** the TUI renders\n   **Then** the task node text is rendered with dim/muted styling\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** an active task in the workflow graph\n   **When** the TUI renders\n   **Then** the task node is rendered in cyan with an animated spinner indicator\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** a completed (done) task in the workflow graph\n   **When** the TUI renders\n   **Then** the task node shows a green checkmark (`ã`)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** a failed task in the workflow graph\n   **When** the TUI renders\n   **Then** the task node shows a red cross (`ã`)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** a task with a configured `driver` field (e.g., `codex`, `opencode`, `claude-code`)\n   **When** the TUI renders the workflow graph\n   **Then** the driver name is displayed as dimmed text below the task node name\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** a completed task node with known cost and elapsed time\n   **When** the TUI renders the workflow graph\n   **Then** cost (formatted as `$X.XX`) and elapsed time (formatted as `Xm` or `Xs`) are displayed below the driver label\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** a completed task where the driver reported `null` cost\n   **When** the TUI renders\n   **Then** cost displays as `...` (not `$0.00`) and elapsed time still renders normally\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n8. **Given** a task transition occurs (e.g., pending to active, active to done)\n   **When** the renderer receives the state update\n   **Then** the workflow graph re-renders within the same render cycle (no artificial delay), satisfying NFR2 (500ms update target)\n   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n\n9. **Given** the `WorkflowGraphProps` interface\n   **When** inspected\n   **Then** it includes a `taskMeta` field of type `Record<string, TaskNodeMeta>` where `TaskNodeMeta` contains `driver?: string`, `costUsd?: number | null`, and `elapsedMs?: number | null`\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n10. **Given** the `RendererHandle` interface\n    **When** inspected\n    **Then** `updateWorkflowState` accepts an additional `taskMeta` parameter of type `Record<string, TaskNodeMeta>`\n    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n11. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n    **When** the build completes\n    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Define `TaskNodeMeta` type and extend props/state (AC: #9, #10)\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `export interface TaskNodeMeta { driver?: string; costUsd?: number | null; elapsedMs?: number | null; }`\n  - [ ] Add `taskMeta: Record<string, TaskNodeMeta>` to `RendererState`\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx`, add `taskMeta` to `WorkflowGraphProps`\n  - [ ] Update `updateWorkflowState` in `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` to accept and store `taskMeta`\n  - [ ] Update `noopHandle` and initial state with `taskMeta: {}`\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Upgrade active status indicator to spinner (AC: #2)\n  - [ ] Add `ink-spinner` as dependency (check if already installed; if not, use a simple text-based spinner or the `Spinner` from `ink`)\n  - [ ] If `ink-spinner` is unavailable, use a cycling character (`ã` ã `ã` ã `ã`) or keep `ã` but render with cyan ã match what Ink supports natively\n  - [ ] Update `TaskNode` in `ink-workflow.tsx`: when status is `active`, render cyan text with spinner indicator\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Add driver label and cost/time below each task node (AC: #5, #6, #7)\n  - [ ] Refactor `WorkflowGraph` from single-line flow to a column layout per node\n  - [ ] Each node column: row 1 = task name + status icon, row 2 = driver label (dim), row 3 = cost/time (dim, only for completed tasks)\n  - [ ] Format cost: `$X.XX` or `...` if null. Format time: `Xm` for >=60s, `Xs` for <60s, `...` if null\n  - [ ] Arrows (`ã`) connect at the top row (task name level)\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#7, #9, #10, #11)\n  - [ ] Update existing tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` for new props shape\n  - [ ] Test: pending task renders dim\n  - [ ] Test: active task renders cyan with spinner element\n  - [ ] Test: done task renders green checkmark\n  - [ ] Test: failed task renders red cross\n  - [ ] Test: driver label renders below task name\n  - [ ] Test: cost/time renders below driver for completed tasks\n  - [ ] Test: null cost renders as `...`\n  - [ ] Test: `taskMeta` prop is accepted and influences rendering\n  - [ ] Update `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` for new `updateWorkflowState` signature\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Verify build and tests (AC: #11)\n  - [ ] Run `npm run build` ã zero TypeScript errors\n  - [ ] Run `npm run test:unit` ã all tests pass, no regressions\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Architecture Compliance\n\nThis story implements Epic 5, Story 5.2 (mapped to sprint Epic 14, Story 14-2) \"Task Status & Driver Labels\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n- **FR26:** System can display the driver name (framework label) under each task node in the workflow graph\n- **FR27:** System can display accumulated cost and elapsed time per completed task node\n- **FR29:** System can update the workflow graph position within 500ms of a task transition\n- **FR30:** System can show task completion status (checkmark, spinner, pending) per node in the workflow graph\n\nKey architecture decisions honored:\n- **Decision 5 (TUI Workflow Graph Component):** Extends the `WorkflowGraph` Ink component with driver labels and cost/time below each node, matching the architecture rendering format.\n\n### Rendering Format Target (from Architecture Decision 5)\n\n```\nããã Workflow: story 3-1 ããããããããããããããããããããããããã\n  implement ã  ã  verify ã  ã  loop(1)[ retry ã verify ]\n  claude-code     codex\n  $0.42 / 4m      ... / 2m\nããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããã\n```\n\nRow 1: task names with status icons, connected by arrows. Row 2: driver labels (dimmed). Row 3: cost/time for completed tasks (dimmed). Pending/active tasks show no cost/time row.\n\n### What Already Exists (from Story 14-1)\n\n- `WorkflowGraph` component in `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` ã renders single-line flow with status indicators (pending dim, active cyan `ã`, done green `ã`, failed red `ã`). Currently NO driver labels, NO cost/time, NO spinner.\n- `TaskNodeState` type in `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` ã `'pending' | 'active' | 'done' | 'failed'`\n- `WorkflowGraphProps` in `ink-workflow.tsx` ã `{ flow, currentTask, taskStates }`. No `taskMeta` yet.\n- `RendererState` in `ink-components.tsx` ã has `workflowFlow`, `currentTaskName`, `taskStates`. No `taskMeta`.\n- `updateWorkflowState(flow, currentTask, taskStates)` in `ink-renderer.tsx` ã currently 3 params. Needs 4th param for `taskMeta`.\n- `noopHandle` in `ink-renderer.tsx` ã needs no-op for new param.\n- `FlowStep`, `LoopBlock`, `ResolvedTask` in `workflow-parser.ts` ã `ResolvedTask` already has `driver?: string`. Do NOT modify these.\n- 9 existing tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` ã must update for new `taskMeta` prop.\n- `makeState` helper in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` ã must add `taskMeta: {}`.\n\n### Data Flow for Driver/Cost Info\n\nThe workflow engine (`workflow-engine.ts`) already has access to:\n- `task.driver` ã from `ResolvedTask.driver` (defaults to `'claude-code'`)\n- `driver.getLastCost()` ã returns `number | null` after dispatch\n- Elapsed time ã computed from dispatch start/end timestamps\n\nThis story does NOT wire the workflow engine to call `updateWorkflowState` with meta. That wiring belongs to a future integration story. This story adds the props, rendering, and tests so the API is ready.\n\n### Spinner Implementation\n\nThe architecture says \"active ã cyan + spinner\". Story 14-1 used `ã` as a simpler placeholder. This story should upgrade:\n- Check if `ink-spinner` is already in `package.json`. If yes, use `<Spinner type=\"dots\" />` from `ink-spinner`.\n- If not available, use a text-based approach: `ã` is acceptable if adding a dependency is undesirable. The key requirement is cyan coloring.\n- Do NOT add a heavy spinner dependency just for this. Check first.\n\n### Format Helpers\n\nCreate small pure functions (in `ink-workflow.tsx` or a shared util):\n- `formatCost(costUsd: number | null | undefined): string` ã returns `$X.XX` or `...`\n- `formatElapsed(ms: number | null | undefined): string` ã returns `Xm`, `Xs`, or `...`\n\nThese are pure, testable, and reusable for story 14-3 (activity display).\n\n### What NOT to Do\n\n- Do NOT wire the workflow engine to pass `taskMeta` ã this story builds the TUI-layer API only. Engine integration is a future story.\n- Do NOT modify `workflow-parser.ts` or `workflow-engine.ts`.\n- Do NOT add cost tracking logic. Cost data arrives as props.\n- Do NOT change `FlowStep`, `LoopBlock`, or `ResolvedTask` types.\n- Do NOT touch `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` ã that is story 14-3.\n- Do NOT break the existing single-line flow layout. The 3-row layout (name, driver, cost) is an extension ã when `taskMeta` is empty, the graph should render identically to the current single-line format.\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence\n\nFrom story 14-1 (WorkflowGraph Component):\n- Component is purely presentational ã no hooks, no side effects, driven by props.\n- `loopIteration()` is a heuristic (counts 0 before start, 1 once started). Proper multi-iteration counting deferred.\n- Tests use `ink-testing-library` `render()` with `lastFrame()` string assertions.\n- `termWidth()` helper caps output width to 80 columns.\n- The `isLoopBlock()` type guard is used for narrowing `FlowStep`.\n- 9 tests pass: sequential flow, loop block, all 4 status states, empty flow/taskStates ã null.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nLast commit: `e427064 feat: story 14-1-workflowgraph-component ã WorkflowGraph TUI Component`\n\nFiles created/modified by 14-1:\n- `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` ã NEW (this is what we modify)\n- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` ã NEW (update tests)\n- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` ã MODIFIED (`TaskNodeState`, `RendererState` extended)\n- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` ã MODIFIED (WorkflowGraph inserted in layout)\n- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` ã MODIFIED (`updateWorkflowState` added)\n- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` ã MODIFIED (`makeState` helper updated)\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\nFiles to MODIFY:\n- `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` ã Add `taskMeta` prop, multi-row node rendering, driver labels, cost/time display, spinner for active state\n- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` ã Add `TaskNodeMeta` interface, add `taskMeta` to `RendererState`\n- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` ã Update `updateWorkflowState` signature to include `taskMeta` param, update implementation and `noopHandle`\n- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` ã Update all tests for new prop shape, add driver/cost/time tests\n- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` ã Update `makeState` helper with `taskMeta: {}`\n\nFiles NOT to modify:\n- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` ã Engine wiring is NOT part of this story\n- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` ã Types already have `driver` field, no changes needed\n- `src/lib/agents/*` ã Driver layer not touched\n- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` ã Layout already correct from 14-1 (WorkflowGraph already in position)\n- `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` ã Activity display is story 14-3\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 5.2: Task Status & Driver Labels]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md ã Decision 5: TUI Workflow Graph Component]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md ã FR26, FR27, FR29, FR30]\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx ã Existing WorkflowGraph component from story 14-1]\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx ã TaskNodeState type, RendererState interface]\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx ã RendererHandle interface, updateWorkflowState, noopHandle]\n- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts ã ResolvedTask.driver field]\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/14-2-task-status-driver-labels-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/14-2-task-status-driver-labels.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\