{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019DMmBw36UEa9mKyd4eDFiB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 14-2 is complete. All 5 tasks implemented, all tests pass (169 files, 4573 tests), build succeeds with zero TypeScript errors, story status set to \"review\".\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n\n1. **`src/lib/ink-components.tsx`** ã Added `TaskNodeMeta` interface (`driver?`, `costUsd?`, `elapsedMs?`) and `taskMeta` field to `RendererState`\n2. **`src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx`** ã Added `taskMeta` to props, replaced `ã` with braille-dot spinner for active tasks, added multi-row layout (driver labels + cost/time below nodes), exported `formatCost`/`formatElapsed` pure helpers\n3. **`src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`** ã Extended `updateWorkflowState` to accept optional 4th `taskMeta` param, added `taskMeta: {}` to initial state, re-exported `TaskNodeMeta`\n4. **`src/lib/ink-app.tsx`** ã Passes `taskMeta` from state to `WorkflowGraph`\n5. **`src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx`** ã 22 tests total (11 updated, 11 new) covering all ACs\n6. **`src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx`** ã `makeState` helper updated with `taskMeta: {}`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Spinner approach**: Used `Date.now()` to derive spinner frame index since the component is pure/stateless (no hooks). This means the spinner only advances when the parent re-renders, not on its own timer. This is acceptable for the current architecture where the renderer re-renders on state changes, but a proper `useInterval` hook would give smoother animation. Left as-is per story constraint (pure presentational component).\n- **Driver/cost row alignment**: The multi-row layout uses simple spacing (`'     '` for arrow gaps) rather than precise column-width calculations. For short task names this looks fine; for very long task names or many tasks, alignment may drift. The architecture target rendering (from Decision 5) shows a similarly approximate layout.\n- **No `ink-spinner` dependency**: Confirmed not installed. Used text-based braille frames per story guidance. No dependency added.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 9, Edit: 10, Grep: 3, Write: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` run 1 (~30 lines), `npm run test:unit` run 2 (~30 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 11 total reads (`ink-workflow.tsx` read 2x, story file read 2x)\n- Redundant operations: Read `ink-workflow.tsx` twice (once before and once after first edit pass to verify state before full rewrite). Acceptable given the rewrite scope."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a666b46e70a53ec23 (use SendMessage with to: 'a666b46e70a53ec23' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60446\ntool_uses: 40\nduration_ms: 273311</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87203133-5cdd-4288-8e5c-bcff0e178735","uuid":"933b3d30-1b19-41bb-82b4-fe06a036f7fe","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:42:26.388Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-2-task-status-driver-labels.md ã implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions ã proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY ã End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY ã Also end your response with a `## Token Report` sec