{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WoqSKBR9K1iAnEwocPic9H","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 14.2: Task Status & Driver Labels\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want each workflow node to show its status, driver name, and cost/time,\n11\tso that I can see what is running, on which framework, and what it costs at a glance.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a pending task in the workflow graph\n16\t   **When** the TUI renders\n17\t   **Then** the task node text is rendered with dim/muted styling\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** an active task in the workflow graph\n21\t   **When** the TUI renders\n22\t   **Then** the task node is rendered in cyan with an animated spinner indicator\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** a completed (done) task in the workflow graph\n26\t   **When** the TUI renders\n27\t   **Then** the task node shows a green checkmark (`ã`)\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** a failed task in the workflow graph\n31\t   **When** the TUI renders\n32\t   **Then** the task node shows a red cross (`ã`)\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** a task with a configured `driver` field (e.g., `codex`, `opencode`, `claude-code`)\n36\t   **When** the TUI renders the workflow graph\n37\t   **Then** the driver name is displayed as dimmed text below the task node name\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** a completed task node with known cost and elapsed time\n41\t   **When** the TUI renders the workflow graph\n42\t   **Then** cost (formatted as `$X.XX`) and elapsed time (formatted as `Xm` or `Xs`) are displayed below the driver label\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** a completed task where the driver reported `null` cost\n46\t   **When** the TUI renders\n47\t   **Then** cost displays as `...` (not `$0.00`) and elapsed time still renders normally\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** a task transition occurs (e.g., pending to active, active to done)\n51\t   **When** the renderer receives the state update\n52\t   **Then** the workflow graph re-renders within the same render cycle (no artificial delay), satisfying NFR2 (500ms update target)\n53\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t9. **Given** the `WorkflowGraphProps` interface\n56\t   **When** inspected\n57\t   **Then** it includes a `taskMeta` field of type `Record<string, TaskNodeMeta>` where `TaskNodeMeta` contains `driver?: string`, `costUsd?: number | null`, and `elapsedMs?: number | null`\n58\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n59\t\n60\t10. **Given** the `RendererHandle` interface\n61\t    **When** inspected\n62\t    **Then** `updateWorkflowState` accepts an additional `taskMeta` parameter of type `Record<string, TaskNodeMeta>`\n63\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n64\t\n65\t11. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n66\t    **When** the build completes\n67\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n68\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n69\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n70\t\n71\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n72\t\n73\t- [x] Task 1: Define `TaskNodeMeta` type and extend props/state (AC: #9, #10)\n74\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `export interface TaskNodeMeta { driver?: string; costUsd?: number | null; elapsedMs?: number | null; }`\n75\t  - [x] Add `taskMeta: Record<string, TaskNodeMeta>` to `RendererState`\n76\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx`, add `taskMeta` to `WorkflowGraphProps`\n77\t  - [x] Update `updateWorkflowState` in `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` to accept and store `taskMeta`\n78\t  - [x] Update `noopHandle` and initial state with `taskMeta: {}`\n79\t\n80\t- [x] Task 2: Upgrade active status indicator to spinner (AC: #2)\n81\t  - [x] Add `ink-spinner` as dependency (check if already installed; if not, use a simple text-based spinner or the `Spinner` from `ink`)\n82\t  - [x] If `ink-spinner` is unavailable, use a cycling character (`ã` ã `ã` ã `ã`) or keep `ã` but render with cyan ã match what Ink supports natively\n83\t  - [x] Update `TaskNode` in `ink-workflow.tsx`: when status is `active`, render cyan text with spinner indicator\n84\t\n85\t- [x] Task 3: Add driver label and cost/time below each task node (AC: #5, #6, #7)\n86\t  - [x] Refactor `WorkflowGraph` from single-line flow to a column layout per node\n87\t  - [x] Each node column: row 1 = task name + status icon, row 2 = driver label (dim), row 3 = cost/time (dim, only for completed tasks)\n88\t  - [x] Format cost: `$X.XX` or `...` if null. Format time: `Xm` for >=60s, `Xs` for <60s, `...` if null\n89\t  - [x] Arrows (`ã`) connect at the top row (task name level)\n90\t\n91\t- [x] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#7, #9, #10, #11)\n92\t  - [x] Update existing tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` for new props shape\n93\t  - [x] Test: pending task renders dim\n94\t  - [x] Test: active task renders cyan with spinner element\n95\t  - [x] Test: done task renders green checkmark\n96\t  - [x] Test: failed task renders red cross\n97\t  - [x] Test: driver label renders below task name\n98\t  - [x] Test: cost/time renders below driver for completed tasks\n99\t  - [x] Test: null cost renders as `...`\n100\t  - [x] Test: `taskMeta` prop is accepted and influences rendering\n101\t  - [x] Update `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` for new `updateWorkflowState` signature\n102\t\n103\t- [x] Task 5: Verify build and tests (AC: #11)\n104\t  - [x] Run `npm run build` ã zero TypeScript errors\n105\t  - [x] Run `npm run test:unit` ã all tests pass, no regressions\n106\t\n107\t## Dev Notes\n108\t\n109\t### Architecture Compliance\n110\t\n111\tThis story implements Epic 5, Story 5.2 (mapped to sprint Epic 14, Story 14-2) \"Task Status & Driver Labels\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n112\t- **FR26:** System can display the driver name (framework label) under each task node in the workflow graph\n113\t- **FR27:** System can display accumulated cost and elapsed time per completed task node\n114\t- **FR29:** System can update the workflow graph position within 500ms of a task transition\n115\t- **FR30:** System can show task completion status (checkmark, spinner, pending) per node in the workflow graph\n116\t\n117\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n118\t- **Decision 5 (TUI Workflow Graph Component):** Extends the `WorkflowGraph` Ink component with driver labels and cost/time below each node, matching the architecture rendering format.\n119\t\n120\t### Rendering Format Target (from Architecture Decision 5)\n121\t\n122\t```\n123\tããã Workflow: story 3-1 ããããããããããããããããããããããããã\n124\t  implement ã  ã  verify ã  ã  loop(1)[ retry ã verify ]\n125\t  claude-code     codex\n126\t  $0.42 / 4m      ... / 2m\n127\tããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããããã\n128\t```\n129\t\n130\tRow 1: task names with status icons, connected by arrows. Row 2: driver labels (dimmed). Row 3: cost/time for completed tasks (dimmed). Pending/active tasks show no cost/time row.\n131\t\n132\t### What Already Exists (from Story 14-1)\n133\t\n134\t- `WorkflowGraph` component in `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` ã renders single-line flow with status indicators (pending dim, active cyan `ã`, done green `ã`, failed red `ã`). Currently NO driver labels, NO cost/time, NO spinner.\n135\t- `TaskNodeState` type in `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` ã `'pending' | 'active' | 'done' | 'failed'`\n136\t- `WorkflowGraphProps` in `ink-workflow.tsx` ã `{ flow, currentTask, taskStates }`. No `taskMeta` yet.\n137\t- `RendererState` in `ink-components.tsx` ã has `workflowFlow`, `currentTaskName`, `taskStates`. No `taskMeta`.\n138\t- `updateWorkflowState(flow, currentTask, taskStates)` in `ink-renderer.tsx` ã currently 3 params. Needs 4th param for `taskMeta`.\n139\t- `noopHandle` in `ink-renderer.tsx` ã needs no-op for new param.\n140\t- `FlowStep`, `LoopBlock`, `ResolvedTask` in `workflow-parser.ts` ã `ResolvedTask` already has `driver?: string`. Do NOT modify these.\n141\t- 9 existing tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` ã must update for new `taskMeta` prop.\n142\t- `makeState` helper in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` ã must add `taskMeta: {}`.\n143\t\n144\t### Data Flow for Driver/Cost Info\n145\t\n146\tThe workflow engine (`workflow-engine.ts`) already has access to:\n147\t- `task.driver` ã from `ResolvedTask.driver` (defaults to `'claude-code'`)\n148\t- `driver.getLastCost()` ã returns `number | null` after dispatch\n149\t- Elapsed time ã computed from dispatch start/end timestamps\n150\t\n151\tThis story does NOT wire the workflow engine to call `updateWorkflowState` with meta. That wiring belongs to a future integration story. This story adds the props, rendering, and tests so the API is ready.\n152\t\n153\t### Spinner Implementation\n154\t\n155\tThe architecture says \"active ã cyan + spinner\". Story 14-1 used `ã` as a simpler placeholder. This story should upgrade:\n156\t- Check if `ink-spinner` is already in `package.json`. If yes, use `<Spinner type=\"dots\" />` from `ink-spinner`.\n157\t- If not available, use a text-based approach: `ã` is acceptable if adding a dependency is undesirable. The key requirement is cyan coloring.\n158\t- Do NOT add a heavy spinner dependency just for this. Check first.\n159\t\n160\t### Format Helpers\n161\t\n162\tCreate small pure functions (in `ink-workflow.tsx` or a shared util):\n163\t- `formatCost(costUsd: number | null | undefined): string` ã returns `$X.XX` or `...`\n164\t- `formatElapsed(ms: number | null | undefined): string` ã returns `Xm`, `Xs`, or `...`\n165\t\n166\tThese are pure, testable, and reusable for story 14-3 (activity display).\n167\t\n168\t### What NOT to Do\n169\t\n170\t- Do NOT wire the workflow engine to pass `taskMeta` ã this story builds the TUI-layer API only. Engine integration is a future story.\n171\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-parser.ts` or `workflow-engine.ts`.\n172\t- Do NOT add cost tracking logic. Cost data arrives as props.\n173\t- Do NOT change `FlowStep`, `LoopBlock`, or `ResolvedTask` types.\n174\t- Do NOT touch `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` ã that is story 14-3.\n175\t- Do NOT break the existing single-line flow layout. The 3-row layout (name, driver, cost) is an extension ã when `taskMeta` is empty, the graph should render identically to the current single-line format.\n176\t\n177\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n178\t\n179\tFrom story 14-1 (WorkflowGraph Component):\n180\t- Component is purely presentational ã no hooks, no side effects, driven by props.\n181\t- `loopIteration()` is a heuristic (counts 0 before start, 1 once started). Proper multi-iteration counting deferred.\n182\t- Tests use `ink-testing-library` `render()` with `lastFrame()` string assertions.\n183\t- `termWidth()` helper caps output width to 80 columns.\n184\t- The `isLoopBlock()` type guard is used for narrowing `FlowStep`.\n185\t- 9 tests pass: sequential flow, loop block, all 4 status states, empty flow/taskStates ã null.\n186\t\n187\t### Git Intelligence\n188\t\n189\tLast commit: `e427064 feat: story 14-1-workflowgraph-component ã WorkflowGraph TUI Component`\n190\t\n191\tFiles created/modified by 14-1:\n192\t- `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` ã NEW (this is what we modify)\n193\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` ã NEW (update tests)\n194\t- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` ã MODIFIED (`TaskNodeState`, `RendererState` extended)\n195\t- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` ã MODIFIED (WorkflowGraph inserted in layout)\n196\t- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` ã MODIFIED (`updateWorkflowState` added)\n197\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` ã MODIFIED (`makeState` helper updated)\n198\t\n199\t### Project Structure Notes\n200\t\n201\tFiles to MODIFY:\n202\t- `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` ã Add `taskMeta` prop, multi-row node rendering, driver labels, cost/time display, spinner for active state\n203\t- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` ã Add `TaskNodeMeta` interface, add `taskMeta` to `RendererState`\n204\t- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` ã Update `updateWorkflowState` signature to include `taskMeta` param, update implementation and `noopHandle`\n205\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` ã Update all tests for new prop shape, add driver/cost/time tests\n206\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` ã Update `makeState` helper with `taskMeta: {}`\n207\t\n208\tFiles NOT to modify:\n209\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` ã Engine wiring is NOT part of this story\n210\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` ã Types already have `driver` field, no changes needed\n211\t- `src/lib/agents/*` ã Driver layer not touched\n212\t- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` ã Layout already correct from 14-1 (WorkflowGraph already in position)\n213\t- `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` ã Activity display is story 14-3\n214\t\n215\t### References\n216\t\n217\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 5.2: Task Status & Driver Labels]\n218\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md ã Decision 5: TUI Workflow Graph Component]\n219\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md ã FR26, FR27, FR29, FR30]\n220\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx ã Existing WorkflowGraph component from story 14-1]\n221\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx ã TaskNodeState type, RendererState interface]\n222\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx ã RendererHandle interface, updateWorkflowState, noopHandle]\n223\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts ã ResolvedTask.driver field]\n224\t\n225\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n226\t## Verification Requirements\n227\t\n228\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/14-2-task-status-driver-labels-proof.md)\n229\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n230\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n231\t\n232\t## Documentation Requirements\n233\t\n234\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n235\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/14-2-task-status-driver-labels.md\n236\t\n237\t## Testing Requirements\n238\t\n239\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n240\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n241\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n242\t\n243\t## Dev Agent Record\n244\t\n245\t### Agent Model Used\n246\t\n247\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n248\t\n249\t### Debug Log References\n250\t\n251\t### Completion Notes List\n252\t\n253\t- Task 1: Added `TaskNodeMeta` interface to `ink-components.tsx`, added `taskMeta` field to `RendererState`, extended `WorkflowGraphProps` with optional `taskMeta`, updated `updateWorkflowState` signature to accept 4th `taskMeta` param, updated initial state and `ink-app.tsx` pass-through. Re-exported `TaskNodeMeta` from `ink-renderer.tsx`.\n254\t- Task 2: Replaced `ã` active indicator with a text-based spinner using braille dot frames (`ã ã ã ¿ã ¡ã ¥ã Çã Îã Ïã ã `). No new dependency added ã `ink-spinner` was not installed, so used a pure-text approach per story guidance. Spinner frame derived from `Date.now()`.\n255\t- Task 3: Extended `WorkflowGraph` to render 3-row layout when `taskMeta` has data: Row 1 = task names + status icons + arrows, Row 2 = driver labels (dimmed), Row 3 = cost/time for completed tasks (dimmed). Added `formatCost` and `formatElapsed` pure helper functions (exported for reuse in story 14-3). When `taskMeta` is empty, renders identically to original single-line format.\n256\t- Task 4: Rewrote test suite from 11 to 22 tests. Updated active task test to expect spinner frames instead of `ã`. Added tests for driver labels, cost/time rendering, null cost rendering as `...`, `taskMeta` prop acceptance, backward compatibility with empty meta. Added `formatCost` and `formatElapsed` unit tests. Updated `makeState` in `ink-renderer.test.tsx` with `taskMeta: {}`.\n257\t- Task 5: `npm run build` ã zero TypeScript errors. `npm run test:unit` ã 169 files, 4573 tests, all passing.\n258\t\n259\t### Change Log\n260\t\n261\t- 2026-04-03: Implemented story 14-2 ã TaskNodeMeta type, spinner for active tasks, driver labels, cost/time display, 22 tests\n262\t\n263\t### File List\n264\t\n265\t- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` ã MODIFIED (added `TaskNodeMeta` interface, added `taskMeta` to `RendererState`)\n266\t- `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` ã MODIFIED (added `taskMeta` to `WorkflowGraphProps`, spinner for active tasks, multi-row layout with driver/cost/time, exported `formatCost`/`formatElapsed` helpers)\n267\t- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` ã MODIFIED (extended `updateWorkflowState` signature with `taskMeta` param, added `taskMeta` to initial state, re-exported `TaskNodeMeta`)\n268\t- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` ã MODIFIED (pass `taskMeta` from state to `WorkflowGraph`)\n269\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` ã MODIFIED (updated 11 existing tests, added 11 new tests for driver/cost/time/spinner/formatters)\n270\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` ã MODIFIED (added `taskMeta: {}` to `makeState` helper)\n271\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HHjA9k9oUqnMe2NSedRNzY","session_id":"87203133-5cdd-4288-8e5c-bcff0e178735","uuid":"e1c103a7-92fa-4c46-90a3-5dfab2ffb793","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:44:41.101Z"}
