MEDIUM** | Misleading comment \"ref-based counter\" with no ref | `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx:113` | Rewrote comment |\n| **MEDIUM** | No test for `formatElapsed(0)` edge case | `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` | Added test |\n| **MEDIUM** | No test for fractional minutes (boundary regression protection) | `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` | Added test with 90s, 150s cases |\n| **MEDIUM** | No test for driver labels within loop blocks | `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` | Added loop-with-meta test |\n\n### Results\n\n- Build: zero TypeScript errors\n- Tests: 169 files, 4576 tests, all passing (3 new tests added)\n- Coverage: 96.85% overall, all 171 files above 80% per-file floor\n- Story status: updated to `verifying`\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `formatElapsed` rounding bug ã `Math.round(seconds/60)` inflated displayed minutes (90s showed \"2m\"). Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Column alignment bug ã driver/cost rows used 5-space separators vs 3-col arrow width. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- Spinner uses `Date.now()` making it non-deterministic in tests. Tests work around this by checking \"any spinner frame\" rather than a specific one. Proper fix would be to inject a clock/frame-counter prop, but this is low priority for a TUI animation.\n- `formatCost(0)` returns `\"$0.00\"` which is technically correct but could be confusing if the driver genuinely reported zero cost vs. unknown cost. The story spec says null = `\"...\"` and the implementation handles that correctly, so this is a design decision, not a bug.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. All files above 80%, overall at 96.85%.\n- No integration test for the full `App` -> `WorkflowGraph` render chain with `taskMeta` populated (unit tests cover the component in isolation).\n- Spinner animation timing not tested (non-deterministic by design).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The column alignment approach (counting spaces manually) is fragile. If task names vary in length, Row 2/3 labels won't align under their respective Row 1 task names. This is a known limitation of text-based column layout without proper width calculation. A future story should use `string-width` to compute proper column padding.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` (~30 lines), `git diff ink-workflow.tsx` (~200 lines), `git diff --name-only` + status (~25 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"}],"totalDurationMs":207589,"totalTokens":55517,"totalToolUseCount":37,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":244,"cache_read_input_tokens":54292,"output_tokens":980,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":244},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
