{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Uc2YvE9BD9m61kcrubwncC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Retrospective ã 2026-04-03\n2\t\n3\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T00:25 to ~2026-04-03T02:00 (approx. 95 minutes)\n4\t**Sprint progress:** 14/28 stories done (50%), Epics 1-4 complete\n5\t\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\t## 1. Session Summary\n9\t\n10\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n11\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n12\t| 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection | verify (tail end) | **Done** | Was already at verify from prior session. 9/9 ACs passed. |\n13\t| 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement | create-story, dev, code-review, verify | **Done** | Full lifecycle in one session. 9/9 ACs, 100% coverage on module. |\n14\t| Epic 4 milestone | ã | **Done** | All 4 stories shipped. Commit `4a35568`. |\n15\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | create-story, dev | **Review** | Story created and implemented. 31 tests, 89.91% coverage. Ran out of time before code-review/verify. |\n16\t\n17\t**Net output:** 2 stories completed + verified, 1 story implemented but not reviewed, 1 epic closed.\n18\t\n19\t---\n20\t\n21\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n22\t\n23\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n24\t\n25\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n26\t|----------|-------|-------|\n27\t| HIGH | 4-3 | `generateTraceId` accepted NaN/Infinity/negative/float iteration values |\n28\t| HIGH | 4-4 | Path traversal via unsanitized `runId` in file path |\n29\t| HIGH | 4-4 | Silent file overwrite on basename collision ã data loss risk |\n30\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | No segment length cap ã unbounded trace IDs possible |\n31\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | `formatTracePrompt('')` produced empty trace marker silently |\n32\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | `workflow-state.ts` coverage at 79.06%, below 80% floor |\n33\t| MEDIUM | 4-4 | Stale workspace contamination from crashed runs |\n34\t| MEDIUM | 4-4 | Missing edge case tests for sanitization/dedup |\n35\t\n36\tAll HIGH and MEDIUM bugs were fixed in the same session. Code review is earning its keep ã 3 HIGH security/correctness bugs caught before merge.\n37\t\n38\t### Known LOW Issues (deferred)\n39\t\n40\t- 4-3: Duplicate trace ID guard missing; empty runId+taskName produces ugly ID; sanitizeSegment strips non-ASCII\n41\t- 4-4: `deduplicateFilename` counter loop unbounded; hardcoded `/tmp/` base path\n42\t\n43\t### Infrastructure Issues\n44\t\n45\t- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure:** The verify command checks global harness state flags (`tests_passed`, `coverage_met`) which are not set by manual test runs. Workaround: verify manually. This is a harness tooling gap.\n46\t- **`AGENTS.md` stale:** Verify command flags missing entries for new modules (`agent-dispatch.ts`, `agent-resolver.ts`, `session-manager.ts`, `trace-id.ts`, `source-isolation.ts`). Documentation debt accumulating ã 5 modules behind now.\n47\t- **Pre-existing TS errors:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 pre-existing type errors unrelated to current work.\n48\t\n49\t---\n50\t\n51\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n52\t\n53\t### Parent-Level Costs (from cost-report.md, prior session data)\n54\t\n55\tThe cost report covers the prior session (stories through Epic 2). Key structural observations:\n56\t\n57\t- **Total API cost:** $37.08 across 288 calls for 7 stories\n58\t- **Avg cost/story:** $4.45\n59\t- **Dominant cost:** Cache reads at 61% ($22.62) ã expected for long-context sessions\n60\t- **Verify phase:** 43.8% of total cost ($16.24) ã nearly half of all spending is on verification\n61\t\n62\t### Subagent Token Report (this session)\n63\t\n64\tAggregated from `.session-issues.md` token reports:\n65\t\n66\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools |\n67\t|---------------|------------|-----------|\n68\t| 4-3 create-story | 14 | Read: 5, Grep: 4, Glob: 3 |\n69\t| 4-3 dev-story | 14 | Edit: 6, Read: 5, Bash: 4 |\n70\t| 4-3 code-review | 23 | Bash: 12, Read: 7, Edit: 5 |\n71\t| 4-3 verification | 12 | Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2 |\n72\t| 4-4 create-story | 12 | Read: 7, Grep: 3 |\n73\t| 4-4 dev-story | 15 | Read: 5, Bash: 4, Grep: 4 |\n74\t| 4-4 code-review | 22 | Bash: 9, Read: 7, Edit: 7 |\n75\t| 4-4 verification | 12 | Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2 |\n76\t| 5-1 create-story | 18 | Read: 12, Glob: 5, Bash: 2 |\n77\t| 5-1 dev-story | 22 | Read: 13, Bash: 6, Edit: 4 |\n78\t| **Total** | **164** | Read: 67, Bash: 51, Edit: 22, Grep: 18 |\n79\t\n80\t### Observations\n81\t\n82\t- **Code review is the most tool-heavy phase** (22-23 calls) ã Bash-heavy because it runs tests after each fix.\n83\t- **Read dominates** at 67/164 calls (41%). The 5-1 create-story phase read 12 unique files ã story creation requires reading architecture, PRD, epics, and existing modules.\n84\t- **Redundant operations detected:**\n85\t  - 4-3 verification: `codeharness verify` called twice\n86\t  - 4-4 verification: Coverage run twice (default + targeted)\n87\t  - 4-4 create-story: Two Grep calls to `source_access` could have been one\n88\t  - 4-3 verification: Architecture doc `architecture-v2.md` read twice\n89\t- **Largest Bash outputs:** Coverage runs (80-160 lines) dominate. Test suite runs are 20-50 lines.\n90\t\n91\t### Estimated session cost\n92\t\n93\tAt ~164 subagent tool calls plus orchestrator overhead, estimated this session cost **$10-14** (extrapolating from prior session's $4.45/story rate, 2.5 story-equivalents completed).\n94\t\n95\t---\n96\t\n97\t## 4. What Went Well\n98\t\n99\t1. **Full-lifecycle velocity:** Story 4-4 went from backlog to verified in a single session (~45 min for create+dev+review+verify). The pipeline is working.\n100\t2. **Code review catching real bugs:** 3 HIGH severity bugs caught (path traversal, data loss, input validation). These would have been production defects."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0165HatmdNrNKJmxCFrwZHY1","session_id":"87203133-5cdd-4288-8e5c-bcff0e178735","uuid":"ff8ade54-2f2c-4ebb-9934-5a92eb4e7c2b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:52:14.080Z"}
