{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TF3uCx9wzQo97vfezDxs1q","type":"tool_result","content":"100\t2. **Code review catching real bugs:** 3 HIGH severity bugs caught (path traversal, data loss, input validation). These would have been production defects.\n101\t3. **Epic 4 completed:** All 4 stories (agent dispatch, session management, trace IDs, source isolation) shipped and verified.\n102\t4. **Test quality:** 100% coverage on both trace-id.ts and source-isolation.ts modules. 31 tests written for 5-1 in dev phase alone.\n103\t5. **Zero retries this session:** All stories completed on first attempt ã no stuck/failed cycles.\n104\t6. **Session issues log is working:** Subagent self-reporting produced actionable data for this retro.\n105\t\n106\t---\n107\t\n108\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n109\t\n110\t1. **Time budget exhaustion:** Story 5-1 got through dev but couldn't complete code-review or verify. It's stuck at \"review\" status ã needs manual follow-up.\n111\t2. **`codeharness verify` is unreliable:** Fails on harness state flags that aren't set during subagent runs. This forced manual verification workarounds in both 4-3 and 4-4.\n112\t3. **AGENTS.md documentation debt:** 5 new modules have no AGENTS.md entries. The verify command flags this every time, burning cycles on a known-stale doc.\n113\t4. **Cost report stale:** `codeharness stats --save` requires `session-logs/` directory which doesn't exist for this session type. The cost report only covers the prior session's data.\n114\t5. **Sprint state file divergence:** `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` shows 4-4 as \"verifying\" and 5-1 as \"backlog\" ã but sprint-status.yaml shows 4-4 as done and 5-1 as review. State files are out of sync.\n115\t\n116\t---\n117\t\n118\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n119\t\n120\t### Patterns to Repeat\n121\t\n122\t- **Code review as a mandatory gate:** Every HIGH bug this session was caught by code review, not tests. The adversarial review phase is load-bearing.\n123\t- **Session issues log:** Self-reported token data from subagents made cost analysis possible without working harness stats.\n124\t- **Pure-logic module design:** Both trace-id and source-isolation achieved 100% coverage because they have no I/O dependencies. This pattern works.\n125\t\n126\t### Patterns to Avoid\n127\t\n128\t- **Running `codeharness verify` without checking preconditions:** Wastes a full invocation cycle. Either fix the verify command or skip it when flags aren't set.\n129\t- **Running coverage twice:** Once is enough. The second targeted run is redundant when the first already reports per-file coverage.\n130\t- **Starting a new story late in a session:** 5-1 was started knowing time was short. It would have been cleaner to stop after Epic 4 closure.\n131\t\n132\t---\n133\t\n134\t## 7. Action Items\n135\t\n136\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n137\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n138\t| 1 | Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1 | HIGH | Next session |\n139\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog |\n140\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` with entries for agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id, source-isolation modules | MEDIUM | Next session |\n141\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Backlog |\n142\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Next session |\n143\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog |\n144\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3 and 4-4 code reviews | LOW | Backlog |\n145\t\n146\t---\n147\t\n148\t# Session Retrospective ã 2026-04-03 (Session 2)\n149\t\n150\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:00Z\n151\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T01:53 to ~2026-04-03T02:15 (approx. 22 minutes)\n152\t**Sprint progress:** 15/28 stories done (53.6%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 started\n153\t\n154\t---\n155\t\n156\t## 1. Session Summary\n157\t\n158\tThis session picked up story 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps at `review` status and drove it to `done`. No new stories were started.\n159\t\n160\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n161\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n162\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | code-review, verification, proof-doc fix, AGENTS.md update | **Done** | 14/14 ACs verified. Commit `b983273`. |\n163\t\n164\t**Activities completed:**\n165\t1. Code review found 2 HIGH bugs and 2 MEDIUM issues ã all fixed\n166\t2. Test-provable verification: 14/14 ACs passed, 3963 tests green, 99.2% stmt coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n167\t3. Proof document formatting fix (needed `**Tier:**` bold format)\n168\t4. `src/lib/AGENTS.md` updated to include `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`\n169\t\n170\t---\n171\t\n172\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n173\t\n174\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n175\t\n176\t| Severity | Issue |\n177\t|----------|-------|\n178\t| HIGH | Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop ã only the inner work-items loop. Catastrophic failures would be silently swallowed. |\n179\t| HIGH | Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Crash recovery would lose track of failed tasks. |\n180\t| MEDIUM | Coverage gaps ã 8 new tests added. Coverage improved to 99.2% stmt / 87% branch. |\n181\t\n182\t### LOW Issues Deferred (not fixed)\n183\t\n184\t- Duplicate checkpoint creation logic in `dispatchTask` else branch\n185\t- `handleDispatchError` and `recordErrorInState` could be merged\n186\t- `warn()` calls for skipped tasks don't propagate to `EngineResult.errors`\n187\t- Branch coverage at 87% ã remaining uncovered branches are defensive null checks on YAML parse results\n188\t- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML mocked)\n189\t\n190\t### Infrastructure Issues\n191\t\n192\t- **AGENTS.md was stale** ã missing entries for `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`. Fixed in this session.\n193\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #1 from Session 1 (\"Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1\") is now done.\n194\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #3 from Session 1 (\"Update AGENTS.md\") is now partially addressed (2 of 5 missing modules added).\n195\t\n196\t---\n197\t\n198\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n199\t\n200\t### Subagent Token Report (this session only)\n201\t\n202\tFrom `.session-issues.md` token reports for the 5-1 phases that ran this session:\n203\t\n204\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools |\n205\t|---------------|------------|-----------|\n206\t| 5-1 code-review | 23 | Read: 10, Bash: 9, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1 |\n207\t| **Session Total** | **23** | Read: 10, Bash: 9, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1 |\n208\t\n209\tNote: The verification phase for 5-1 is not in the session issues log ã it likely ran as part of the orchestrator or was not instrumented. The proof document and AGENTS.md update were additional orchestrator-level actions.\n210\t\n211\t### Observations\n212\t\n213\t- **Read-heavy session:** 10/23 tool calls (43%) were Read. Code review needs to read the implementation, tests, architecture, and existing code to find bugs.\n214\t- **Bash-heavy for code review:** 9 Bash calls ã running tests after each fix. This is inherent to the fix-verify loop.\n215\t- **Redundant operations:** Coverage grep ran 3 times with different patterns (could be 1 call with combined pattern).\n216\t- **Largest Bash outputs:** Coverage run (~80 lines), vitest full suite (~10 lines), git diff --name-only (~11 lines).\n217\t- **Estimated session cost:** ~$3-4 (1 code-review phase + verification + minor fixups). This session was efficient ã minimal waste.\n218\t\n219\t### Cumulative Cost Tracking\n220\t\n221\t| Session | Stories Completed | Estimated Cost | Cost/Story |\n222\t|---------|-------------------|---------------|------------|\n223\t| Prior sessions (Epics 1-2) | 7 | $37.08 | $4.45 |\n224\t| Session 1 (2026-04-03, early) | 2.5 | ~$12 | ~$4.80 |\n225\t| Session 2 (2026-04-03, late) | 0.5 (review+verify) | ~$3.50 | ~$7.00* |\n226\t\n227\t*Higher per-story cost for Session 2 is misleading ã this was just the tail end (review+verify) of a story that was mostly built in Session 1.\n228\t\n229\t---\n230\t\n231\t## 4. What Went Well\n232\t\n233\t1. **Code review found 2 critical flow-control bugs.** The outer loop would have silently continued past catastrophic errors (RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK, SDK_INIT). This is exactly the kind of bug that only shows up in production.\n234\t2. **Clean verification:** 14/14 ACs passed on first attempt. No re-runs needed.\n235\t3. **AGENTS.md debt partially cleared.** Two missing module entries added.\n236\t4. **Focused session:** Single story, single goal, completed efficiently in ~22 minutes.\n237\t5. **Action items from Session 1 addressed:** The top priority action item (complete 5-1 review) is done.\n238\t\n239\t---\n240\t\n241\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n242\t\n243\t1. **AGENTS.md still has gaps.** Only `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts` were added. Still missing: `agent-dispatch.ts`, `agent-resolver.ts`, `session-manager.ts`, `trace-id.ts`.\n244\t2. **Verification phase not instrumented.** No token report for the 5-1 verification subagent ã either it wasn't logged or ran inline. This is a gap in observability.\n245\t3. **`codeharness stats` still broken** for non-ralph sessions. No session-logs directory exists. Cost analysis relies entirely on manual extrapolation from subagent token reports.\n246\t4. **Coverage grep ran 3 times** during code review with different patterns ã minor waste but symptomatic of the \"grep-and-check\" loop.\n247\t\n248\t---\n249\t\n250\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n251\t\n252\t### Patterns to Repeat\n253\t\n254\t- **Review-then-verify in a dedicated session works.** Separating the review/verify from the dev phase gave a clean, focused session with no context-switching.\n255\t- **Code review on flow-control logic is essential.** Error-handling paths in orchestrators are where the worst bugs hide. Both HIGH bugs were in error-handling branches.\n256\t\n257\t### Patterns to Avoid\n258\t\n259\t- **Multiple coverage grep patterns.** Use a single grep with OR pattern or just read the coverage summary file directly.\n260\t- **Leaving AGENTS.md updates incomplete.** If updating, update all missing entries in one pass ã don't leave partial debt.\n261\t\n262\t---\n263\t\n264\t## 7. Action Items\n265\t\n266\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n267\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n268\t| 1 | ~~Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1~~ | ~~HIGH~~ | ~~Next session~~ | DONE |\n269\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog | Open |\n270\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` ã still missing: agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id | MEDIUM | Next session | Partial |\n271\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n272\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Next session | Open |\n273\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n274\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3, 4-4, and 5-1 code reviews | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n275\t| 8 | Add integration test for actual YAML parsing (not mocked) in workflow-engine | LOW | Backlog | New |\n276\t\n277\t---\n278\t\n279\t# Session Retrospective ã 2026-04-03 (Session 3)\n280\t\n281\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:45Z\n282\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T02:12 to ~2026-04-03T02:39 (approx. 27 minutes)\n283\t**Sprint progress:** 17/28 stories done (60.7%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 at 2/4\n284\t\n285\t---\n286\t\n287\t## 1. Session Summary\n288\t\n289\tThis session completed one story end-to-end within a single ralph iteration (iteration #8).\n290\t\n291\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n292\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n293\t| 5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks | create-story, dev-story, code-review, test-provable verification | **Done** | Full lifecycle in ~27 minutes. 10/10 ACs passed. Commit `1219d18`. |\n294\t\n295\t**Key deliverables:**\n296\t- `executeLoopBlock()` ã loop block execution with termination on pass/maxIterations/circuit-breaker\n297\t- `parseVerdict()` ã EvaluatorVerdict JSON parsing from dispatch output\n298\t- `buildRetryPrompt()` ã finding injection into retry prompts\n299\t- `getFailedItems()` ã failed-story-only retry filtering"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0165HatmdNrNKJmxCFrwZHY1","session_id":"87203133-5cdd-4288-8e5c-bcff0e178735","uuid":"cef84312-aeae-4e48-9c5e-68859a053500","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:52:22.380Z"}
